<subsubsection xml:id="lec-representarDatosYResolverProblemas-sintesis" component="profesor">
  <shorttitle><custom ref="synthesis-leccion-titulo"/></shorttitle>
  <title><custom ref="synthesis-leccion-titulo"/></title>
  <title component="profesor"><nbsp/>([@@@@@@@@@] mins)</title>

  <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
  <p>Display a student-created bar graph.</p>
<p>Generate a few questions for students to answer about how they get home using the bar graph. For example, you might ask:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<q>¿Cuántos estudiantes más <fillin></fillin> que <fillin></fillin>?</q></li>
<li>
<q>¿Cuántos estudiantes menos <fillin></fillin> que <fillin></fillin>?</q></li>
<li>
<q>¿Cuántos estudiantes más <fillin></fillin> o <fillin></fillin> que <fillin></fillin>?</q></li>
</ul>
<p>Have students answer the questions and share their reasoning.</p>
<p><strong>Math Community</strong></p>
<p>After the Cool-down, give students 2–3 minutes to discuss any revisions to the <q>Doing Math</q> actions in small groups. Share ideas as a whole group and record any revisions.</p>

</subsubsection>



